6 Conclusion

  • For the survival model, we utilize PCA, LASSO, and AIC to select the variables. (see Remark)
  • PCA map display the most of variables are lying on the x-axis and y-axis, it means they are from the same direction.
  • Results of LASSO and AIC (see \(\text{Table}\:\text{1}\))
\(\text{Table}\:\text{1.}\)Variables Selection for Models and Methods
Model Method Grade Configuration Invasiveness pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin UC
OS LASSO Invasiveness pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin UC
AIC pT stage PNI Surgical margin
CS LASSO pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin UC
AIC pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin
DFS LASSO Invasiveness pT stage LVI PNI Surgical margin UC
AIC Invasiveness LVI PNI Surgical margin
BRFS LASSO Configuration
AIC Configuration


  • Clearly, Grade is dropped.
  • pT stage, LVI, PNI, and Surgical margin are selected from the methods because, except for the “BRFS” model, these variables are effective for the model.
  • In the “BRFS” model, AIC only selects Configuration, and LASSO drops all variables. Even if we add pT stage, LVI, PNI, and Surgical margin into the model, these methods still drop them all.

Remark

  • PCA, dimension reduction, is used to check the relationship between variables.
  • LASSO, regression, is a method for variables/feature selection.
  • AIC, measure of model, is a method for model selection.
